From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: clinglite <clinglite@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Build clingUserInterface unconditionally

The UserInterface library is gated behind CLING_INCLUDE_TESTS, but it
is a runtime dependency of cling.exe, libcling.dll, libclingJupyter.dll,
and clinglite. When building with -DLLVM_INCLUDE_TESTS=OFF (which
propagates to CLING_INCLUDE_TESTS=OFF), clingUserInterface is silently
skipped, causing link failures at the very end of the build.

Remove the CLING_INCLUDE_TESTS guard so UserInterface is always built.
---
 lib/CMakeLists.txt | 4 +---
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/lib/CMakeLists.txt b/lib/CMakeLists.txt
index eb29252..63d4f1e 100644
--- a/lib/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/lib/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -8,7 +8,5 @@
 
 add_subdirectory(Interpreter)
 add_subdirectory(MetaProcessor)
-if(CLING_INCLUDE_TESTS)
-   add_subdirectory(UserInterface)
-endif()
+add_subdirectory(UserInterface)
 add_subdirectory(Utils)
